  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 254 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 648 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 - 3 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 - \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "648 people from 254 families affected in Nuwara Eliya - 3 people lost their lives - Nalvar Mayam - District Governor",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "648 people belonging to 254 families have been evacuated due to the heavy rains and winds that have been falling continuously for two days in Nuwara Eliya District, Nuwara Eliya District Government President Nandana Kalakoda said.",
        "He informed that 3 people died in these incidents and 4 others were swept away in the water and the affected families were sheltered in relative's houses and in temporary places.",
        "We are going to take steps to get compensation to the families of the deceased. We have also taken steps to provide dry food items to the affected families.",
        "He also said that more people have been affected in Ambakamuwa, Kothmalai, Nuwara Eliya and Talawakkalai areas.",
        "Thus, one person died and two houses were damaged due to landslides in Notton-Bridge Deplo area.",
        "The person was trapped in the landslide and died and his body was recovered by the police and army.",
        "The deceased was a 39-year-old resident of Deblo residential area, the police media department said.",
        "A woman and a man have gone missing after being caught in floods in the Navalapitti-Ketapula Akkaravatta area.",
        "It is also worth noting that a 5-year-old girl and her grandmother drowned in Kinikathenai-Polpiti area."
      ],
